{"title_page": "Christian Theodor Ludwig Lucas", "text_new": "'''Christian Theodor Ludwig Lucas''', also known as '''Ludwig Lucas''' or '''C.T.L. Lucas''' (born 1796 in [[Piotrk\u00f3w Trybunalski|Petrikau]], [[South Prussia]] \u2014 d. 1854 in [[\u015arem|Schrimm]], [[Posen Province]]) was a German writer and [[pedagogue]].<ref>[https://tools.wmflabs.org/persondata/p/Ludwig_Lucas Personensuche]</ref>\n\n== Life ==\nLucas enrolled to study, first [[Protestant Theology]] and then law at the [[University of K\u00f6nigsberg]] in 1816. In March 1818, he represented the K\u00f6nigsberger [[Landsmannschaft (Studentenverbindung)|Landsmannschaft]] ([[Burschenschaft|fraternity]]) on the ''Allgemeinen Deutschen Burschenschaft'' (ADB) in [[Jena]].<ref>Eduard Loch: ''Geschichte des Corps Masovia'', 1. K\u00f6nigsberg i. Pr. 1930</ref>  On behalf of [[Theodor von Sch\u00f6n]], Oberpr\u00e4sident (Governor) of [[West Prussia]] he organised the libraries and archives of the monasteries, following the [[Dissolution (law)|dissolution]] of 1818\u20131835. In 1820 he began an academic career. In 1822 he became a teacher at the [[Altstadt Gymnasium]] in [[K\u00f6nigsberg]], in 1828 he served on Government School Board as an assistant to [[Gustav Friedrich Dinter]] and in 1832 became director of the newly reorganised [[Kneiphof Gymnasium]]. By 1835 he was an associate professor of German literature. Succeeding Reinhold Bernhard Jachmann, he served on the Provincial School Board for East Prussia in 1843, and in 1848 transferred to Posen Province.<ref>Robert Albinus: ''K\u00f6nigsberg Lexikon''. W\u00fcrzburg 2002, {{ISBN|3-88189-441-1}}</ref>\n\n==Influence ==\nHe is best known in the English literature the influence of his writing on [[legend]]s on [[Wagner]], in particular the role of ''\u00dcber den Krieg von Wartburg'' (1836) in inspiring the opera [[Tannh\u00e4user (opera)|''Tannh\u00e4user und der S\u00e4ngerkrieg auf Wartburg'']] (1845).{{sfn|Westernhagen|1981|loc=[https://books.google.ca/books?id=QDQ7AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA70 p.&nbsp;70]}} Through the work of Lucas, Wagner learned much about [[Mediaeval]] [[saga]], as he put it \"The German Middle Ages in a significant coloring I had not yet dreamed of\". Wagner also drew on Lucas for his ''[[Lohengrin (opera)|Lohengrin]]'', ''[[Parsifal]]'' and ''[[Tristan und Isolde]]'' operas.{{sfn|Kinderman|2013|loc=[https://books.google.ca/books?id=IQBsjbvFgW4C&pg=PA54 pp.&nbsp;54\u201356]}}{{sfn|Borchmeyer|2003}}\n\n== Selected publications ==\nInclude:<ref>[https://portal.dnb.de/opac.htm?method=simpleSearch&cqlMode=true&query=idn%3D126732914 DNB]</ref>{{sfn|Hathi Trust|2015}}\n*  ''Geschichtliche Nachrichten von [[Malbork|Stadt]] und Schlo\u00df Marienburg in Preu\u00dfen''. In: ''Beitr\u00e4ge zur Kunde Ostpreu\u00dfens'', Vol. 2, K\u00f6nigsberg 1819\n** Erster Abschnitt: ''Von der Gr\u00fcndung der Stadt Marienburg bis zur Erhebung derselben zum Sitze des Hohmeisters (1309)'', p.&nbsp;238-254,   [https://books.google.com/books?id=l9kAAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA238 online]\n** Zweiter Abschnitt:  ''Von der Erhebung Marienburgs zum Sitze des Hochmeisters bis zum Ende der Regierung Winrichs von Kniprode (1309-1382)'', p.&nbsp;306-334, [https://books.google.com/books?id=l9kAAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA306 online].\n* ''De bellis Suantopolici, ducis Pomeranorum, adversus ordinem gestis Teutonicum liber'', Dissertation an der [[Albertus-Universit\u00e4t K\u00f6nigsberg]], 8. May 1823.\n* ''\u00dcber Klopstock's dichterisches Leben und Wirken'', K\u00f6nigsberg 1824.\n* ''Prolog zur \u00f6ffentlichen Sitzung der K\u00f6niglichen Deutschen Gesellschaft am 3. August 1838'' (Gedicht). In: ''Preu\u00dfische Provinzial-Bl\u00e4tter'', 20. Band, K\u00f6nigsberg 1838, S. 477-479, [https://books.google.com/books?id=0t0OAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA477 online].\n* ''\u00dcber den dichterischen Plan von Goethe's Faust''. 2. ed., K\u00f6nigsberg 1846, [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_zd1EAQAAIAAJ online.]\n* {{cite book|last1=Lucas|first1=Ludwig|authorlink = CTL Lucas|title=Ueber den Krieg von Wartburg|date=1838|publisher=Gebr. Borntr\u00e4ger|location=K\u00f6nigsberg|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=VMFaAAAAcAAJ}}, in ''Historische und litterarische Abhandlungen der k\u00f6niglichen deutschen Gesellschaft zu K\u00f6nigsberg'' (Schubert, FW ed.)\n**{{cite web|title=Deutsche Gesellschaft in K\u00f6nigsberg (Royal German Society of K\u00f6nigsberg)|url=http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/1741dgk.html|website=Scholarly Societies Project|publisher=University of Waterloo|accessdate=2 November 2015|date=2015|format=''Historische und literaerische Abhandlungen der [[:de:K\u00f6niglichen Deutschen Gesellschaft zu K\u00f6nigsberg]]''|ref={{harvid|DGK|2015}}|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151103193628/http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/1741dgk.html|archive-date=3 November 2015|url-status=dead}}\n* ''Zur Erinnerung an [[Simon Dach]]. Ein Vortrag in der K\u00f6niglichen Deutschen Gesellschaft am 15. October 1847 gehalten.'' In: '' Neue Preu\u00dfische Provinzial-Bl\u00e4tter'', K\u00f6nigsberg  1847, p.&nbsp;437-447, [https://books.google.com/books?id=zgYBAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA433 online].\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Westernhagen|first1=Curt von |title=Wagner : a biography|date=1981|origyear=1979|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=9780521282543|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=QDQ7AAAAIAAJ|others=Whittall, Mary - translator, originally published by Atlantis Musikbuch-Verlag |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Kinderman|first1=William|title=Wagner's Parsifal|date=2013|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=New York|isbn=9780195366921|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=IQBsjbvFgW4C|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Borchmeyer|first1= Dieter| title=Drama and the world of Richard Wagner|date=2003|publisher=Princeton University Press|location=Princeton, N.J.|isbn=9780691114972|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=7pvwl0wD1lkC|others=Ellis, Daphne - translator|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|last1=Hathi Trust|title=Lucas, Christian Theodor Ludwig|url=http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Lucas,%20Christian%20Theodor%20Ludwig.%22&type=author&inst=|accessdate=11 November 2015|date=2015|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lucas, Christian Theodor Ludwig}}\n[[Category:People from Prussia]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n[[Category:1796 births]]\n[[Category:1854 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "'''Christian Theodor Ludwig Lucas''', also known as '''Ludwig Lucas''' or '''C.T.L. Lucas''' (born 1796 in [[Piotrk\u00f3w Trybunalski|Petrikau]], [[South Prussia]] \u2014 d. 1854 in [[\u015arem|Schrimm]], [[Posen Province]]) was a German writer and [[pedagogue]].<ref>[https://tools.wmflabs.org/persondata/p/Ludwig_Lucas Personensuche]</ref>\n\n== Life ==\nLucas enrolled to study, first [[Protestant Theology]] and then law at the [[University of K\u00f6nigsberg]] in 1816. In March 1818, he represented the K\u00f6nigsberger [[Landsmannschaft (Studentenverbindung)|Landsmannschaft]] ([[Burschenschaft|fraternity]]) on the ''Allgemeinen Deutschen Burschenschaft'' (ADB) in [[Jena]].<ref>Eduard Loch: ''Geschichte des Corps Masovia'', 1. K\u00f6nigsberg i. Pr. 1930</ref>  On behalf of [[Theodor von Sch\u00f6n]], Oberpr\u00e4sident (Governor) of [[West Prussia]] he organised the libraries and archives of the monasteries, following the [[Dissolution (law)|dissolution]] of 1818\u20131835. In 1820 he began an academic career. In 1822 he became a teacher at the [[Altstadt Gymnasium]] in [[K\u00f6nigsberg]], in 1828 he served on Government School Board as an assistant to [[Gustav Friedrich Dinter]] and in 1832 became director of the newly reorganised [[Kneiphof Gymnasium]]. By 1835 he was an associate professor of German literature. Succeeding Reinhold Bernhard Jachmann, he served on the Provincial School Board for East Prussia in 1843, and in 1848 transferred to Posen Province.<ref>Robert Albinus: ''K\u00f6nigsberg Lexikon''. W\u00fcrzburg 2002, {{ISBN|3-88189-441-1}}</ref>\n\n==Influence ==\nHe is best known in the English literature the influence of his writing on [[legend]]s on [[Wagner]], in particular the role of ''\u00dcber den Krieg von Wartburg'' (1836) in inspiring the opera [[Tannh\u00e4user (opera)|''Tannh\u00e4user und der S\u00e4ngerkrieg auf Wartburg'']] (1845).{{sfn|Westernhagen|1981|loc=[https://books.google.ca/books?id=QDQ7AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA70 p.&nbsp;70]}} Through the work of Lucas, Wagner learned much about [[Mediaeval]] [[saga]], as he put it \"The German Middle Ages in a significant coloring I had not yet dreamed of\". Wagner also drew on Lucas for his ''[[Lohengrin (opera)|Lohengrin]]'', ''[[Parsifal]]'' and ''[[Tristan und Isolde]]'' operas.{{sfn|Kinderman|2013|loc=[https://books.google.ca/books?id=IQBsjbvFgW4C&pg=PA54 pp.&nbsp;54\u201356]}}{{sfn|Borchmeyer|2003}}\n\n== Selected publications ==\nInclude:<ref>[https://portal.dnb.de/opac.htm?method=simpleSearch&cqlMode=true&query=idn%3D126732914 DNB]</ref>{{sfn|Hathi Trust|2015}}\n*  ''Geschichtliche Nachrichten von [[Malbork|Stadt]] und Schlo\u00df Marienburg in Preu\u00dfen''. In: ''Beitr\u00e4ge zur Kunde Ostpreu\u00dfens'', Vol. 2, K\u00f6nigsberg 1819\n** Erster Abschnitt: ''Von der Gr\u00fcndung der Stadt Marienburg bis zur Erhebung derselben zum Sitze des Hohmeisters (1309)'', p.&nbsp;238-254,   [https://books.google.com/books?id=l9kAAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA238 online]\n** Zweiter Abschnitt:  ''Von der Erhebung Marienburgs zum Sitze des Hochmeisters bis zum Ende der Regierung Winrichs von Kniprode (1309-1382)'', p.&nbsp;306-334, [https://books.google.com/books?id=l9kAAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA306 online].\n* ''De bellis Suantopolici, ducis Pomeranorum, adversus ordinem gestis Teutonicum liber'', Dissertation an der [[Albertus-Universit\u00e4t K\u00f6nigsberg]], 8. May 1823.\n* ''\u00dcber Klopstock's dichterisches Leben und Wirken'', K\u00f6nigsberg 1824.\n* ''Prolog zur \u00f6ffent